cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DM. 

The paper deals with a machine learning problem of compressing categorical features with large vocabularies, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces a novel re-parametrization of the mutual information objective, which involves optimization techniques, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely category. The paper also deals with information retrieval and feature selection, which are related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), respectively. Finally, the paper involves submodular optimization, which is a topic in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
